Description: Standing bronze figure of a double headed god, with the face of a ram at the front and a jackal at the back. Headdress of horns and tall feathers. Arms bent at the elbows and hands clenched. On a small rectangular plinth.
Exhibition history: Exhibited: 2007/08 Nov-Jan, BM, Room 3, Divine Cat: Speaking to the gods in ancient Egypt
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Sheikh Ali Abd-el-Hai el-Gabri
